LONDON, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Two suspects in the Stephen Lawrence murder case and one other man were arrested Monday on suspicion of theft by Kent Police, police said. 

 A spokeswoman for Kent Police told local reporters three men were arrested in the early hours of Monday morning on suspicion of theft. They were now in custody at a police station. 

 She added that they had been arrested "in the vicinity of the alleged theft." 

 Black teeager Stephen Lawrence was stabbed to death at a bus-stop in Eltham, south London by five white youngsters six years ago. No one has been convicted of the murder. 

